<sect1 id="dolphin" xreflabel="Dolphin-&dolphin-version;">
  <?dbhtml filename="dolphin.html"?>

  <title>Dolphin-&dolphin-version;</title>

  <indexterm zone="dolphin">
    <primary sortas="a-dolphin">Dolphin</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduction to Dolphin</title>

    <para>
      The <application>Dolphin</application> package (not to be confused with
      the <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/kde/dolphin.html">KF6 dolphin file
      manager</ulink>) provides a GCN and Wii emulator.
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Package Information</bridgehead>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Download (HTTP): <ulink url="&dolphin-download-http;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Dolphin Dependencies</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Required</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/cmake.html">CMake</ulink>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/x7driver.html#libevdev">libevdev</ulink>,
      &opengl;,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/qt6.html">Qt-6</ulink>, and
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/x7lib.html">Xorg Libraries</ulink>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Recommended</bridgehead>
    <para role="recommended">
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/multimedia/alsa-utils.html">alsa-utils</ulink>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/bluez.html">BlueZ</ulink>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/basicnet/curl.html">cURL</ulink>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/multimedia/ffmpeg.html">FFmpeg</ulink>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/fmt.html">fmt</ulink>,
      <xref linkend="libspng"/>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/libusb.html">libusb</ulink>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/libxkbcommon.html">libxkbcommon</ulink>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/libxml2.html">libxml2</ulink>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/general/llvm.html">LLVM</ulink>,
      &logind;,
      <!--
      <xref linkend="mgba"/>,
      -->
      <xref linkend="minizip"/>,
      <xref linkend="pugixml"/>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/multimedia/pulseaudio.html">PulseAudio</ulink>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/multimedia/sdl2.html">SDL2</ulink>,
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/multimedia/speex.html">Speex</ulink>, and
      <ulink url="&blfs-svn;/x/vulkan-loader.html">Vulkan-Loader</ulink>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Optional</bridgehead>
    <para role="optional">
      <ulink url="&arch-pkgs;/extra/x86_64/hidapi/">hidapi</ulink> and
      <ulink url="&arch-pkgs;/extra/x86_64/mbedtls/">mbedtls</ulink>
    </para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
    <title>Downloading Dolphin</title>

    <para>
      First, download the package with all its submodules using <ulink
      url="&blfs-svn;/general/git.html">Git</ulink>:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>git clone --recursive &dolphin-download-http; &amp;&amp;
cd dolphin &amp;&amp;
git checkout &dolphin-version;</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of Dolphin</title>

    <para>
      Install <application>Dolphin</application> by running the following
      commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>mkdir build &amp;&amp;
cd    build &amp;&amp;

cmake -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr   \
      -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release    \
      -D CMAKE_SKIP_INSTALL_RPATH=ON \
      -D ENABLE_TESTS=OFF            \
      -G Ninja .. &amp;&amp;

ninja</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>ninja install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>
  
  <sect2 role="commands">
    <title>Command Explanations</title>

    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
      href="../../xincludes/cmake-skip-install-rpath.xml"/>

    <para>
      <parameter>-D ENABLE_TESTS=OFF</parameter>: This parameter disables
      building unit tests.
    </para>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
    <title>Using Dolphin</title>

    <para>
      Using <application>Dolphin</application> is generally straight forward.
      However, if you are on <application>Wayland</application>, and are not
      launching the application via a launcher, then the program will most
      likely not have a variable set in the same breath, which leads to
      <application>Dolphin</application> not being able to launch any game.
      You need to run
      <computeroutput>env QT_QPA_PLATFORM=xcb dolphin-emu</computeroutput> in
      order to bypass this. You might want to set an alias for
      <command>dolphin-emu</command> which includes the
      <computeroutput>env QT_QPA_PLATFORM=xcb</computeroutput> bit, ensuring
      no matter how the program is launched, it has the variable set.
      This variable will be set if the method of launching reads from the
      <filename>.desktop</filename> file, which not all launchers read from.
    </para>

  </sect2>

